Longfellow is handwoven with bamboo, merino wool and a silk-wool blend, its lightweight yet quite warm with a lovely softness and drape, measures 16" W x 65" L. It's rich ink blue, heather grey and thin bands of subtle ice blue cull to mind images of a moody Atlantic Sea and Portland, Maine's Casco Bay on a stormy winter's day. Named after Henry Wadsworth Longfellow a poet born in Portland, Maine in the early 1800's whose poems have had an inspiration on this collection. 

An excerpt from Longfellow's poem Agassiz; 
I stand again on the familiar shore,
And hear the waves of the distracted sea
Piteously calling and lamenting thee,
And waiting restless at thy cottage door.
The rocks, the sea-weed on the ocean floor,
The willows in the meadow, and the free
Wild winds of the Atlantic welcome me...

